    "actual_writers_of_route_tree_gen_ts": [
      "vite build (server-tree generator, adds `declare module` footer)",
      "vite dev (client-tree generator, strips footer on subsequent reprocessing)",
      "vite build --mode development (does not add footer)"
    ],
    "root_cause": "The @tanstack/start-plugin-core route-tree-footer generator always appends the `declare module '@tanstack/react-start'` block during full server-tree generation, while the client-tree generator used by `vite dev` and `build:dev` rewrites the file without it. This produces oscillation between GENERATED_FOOTER_COUNT=0 and =1 depending on which process wrote last.",
    "footer_toggle_available_via_config": false,
    "resolution": "Strategy B — dedicated declaration file (src/tanstack-start-register.d.ts) as single canonical source. vite.config.ts adds a scoped `lsr02:strip-tanstack-start-register-footer` plugin (scope: tanstack_start_registration_only) that removes the auto-generated footer from src/routeTree.gen.ts on buildStart, writeBundle, closeBundle, and configureServer, ensuring GENERATED_FOOTER_COUNT=0 across every generation path."
  },

